    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 966511,
      "reputation" : 9028,
      "user_id" : 989857,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4c2069752c78a37a40291865b26e2343?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "stones333",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/989857/stones333"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 100,
    "last_activity_date" : 1531987976,
    "last_edit_date" : 1531987976,
    "creation_date" : 1350342740,
    "answer_id" : 12905282,
    "question_id" : 12114174,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><code>-XX:PermSize -XX:MaxPermSize</code> are used to set size for Permanent Generation. </p>\n\n<p>Permanent Generation: The Permanent Generation is where class files are kept. These are the result of compiled classes and JSP pages. If this space is full, it triggers a Full Garbage Collection. If the Full Garbage Collection cannot clean out old unreferenced classes and there is no room left to expand the Permanent Space, an Out‐of‐ Memory error (OOME) is thrown and the JVM will crash. </p>\n"
  }, {
